38:43.421 --> 38:44.389 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
else.

38:44.422 --> 38:44.989 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DAVID LORDKIPANIDZE: Not for a
paleontologist.

38:45.023 --> 38:46.791 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

38:46.824 --> 38:50.628 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: But there are
few better
places for a writer gauging the
crosscurrents

38:50.662 --> 38:56.100 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of history. So, with sunset not
far off, Paul
and I walked to the top of the
citadel that

38:56.134 --> 39:01.573 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
