blink of an eye geologically
speaking, the

39:01.606 --> 39:07.679 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
majesty of this place clear,
spread out before
us, and perhaps a key to its
fraught and important

39:07.712 --> 39:08.746 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
past.

39:08.780 --> 39:11.182 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, why is this place such a
crossroads?

39:11.216 --> 39:16.721 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SALOPEK: Well, it's an
antique bridge
between Asia and Europe and has
been for millennia.

39:16.754 --> 39:23.294 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And there has been migration
routes through
here going back before memory.

39:23.328 --> 39:29.100 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The silk road passes through
here. But it
also is the epicenter where
three major empires

39:29.133 --> 39:35.707 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
meet. And they have always
contested this
area. From the south, the
Persians, from the

39:35.740 --> 39:41.145 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
West, the Ottoman Empire, which
is today Turkey,
